== Overview ==

Puppet is an automated configuration tool written in [[RubyLanguage|Ruby]], it is programmed using a DSL and uses ERB templates.

== Major Mode ==

Puppet Labs the developers of puppet have released a major mode that provides syntax highlighting [[https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppet-syntax-emacs|puppet-syntax-emacs]].

== Flymake ==

There is also a Flymake plugin [[https://github.com/grimradical/puppet-flymake|puppet-flymake]] which uses [[https://github.com/rodjek/puppet-lint|puppet-lint]] to do syntax checking.
